begin_memory_text: We exchanged names, talked about our locales, and what we were currently doing in life.  We also discussed how Covid had impacted our lives over the last 6 months.
middle_memory_text: We primarily talked about his career aspirations and how he enjoyed going to a university in a different country.  He discussed his surprise at the beauty and  cleanliness of Toronto.
end_memory_text: Surprisingly he asked me to share any final wisdom I might have for someone of his generation... he said he felt that intergenerational sharing was largely missing from our culture.  He is a very sincere young man.
rest_of_day_open: I think it should be a lot of fun.  My son and daughter-in-law are coming in for a birthday celebration for my wife, as is my oldest son.  Plus, it is the weekend, so I hope to get some additional rest.  On Sunday we have a new preacher filling in for us and I look forward to meeting him and hearing him preach.  Great times!
critical_positive: I think that the best thing about the conversation was that although it started slowly, we both developed a concern for each other and were able to communicate effectively.  I think we developed a rapport, and a genuine interest in each other. I would love to know how his life turns out.
critical_negative: On my end, I had a section in which I became tongue tied and stumbled quite a bit, but we were able laugh it off.  Truthfully, we did not really have any dead period and things went very well.  I thought we both shared well and shared time fairly equally.

begin_memory_text: We talked about what locations of the US we were in, since it was still sunny outside for me but not for him. Shortly afterwards we talked about our professions/occupations.
middle_memory_text: We mainly discussed covid and how it affected us. We also talked a bit about my and his kids' experiences in school and workplace endeavors.
end_memory_text: I asked for any advice he had, as he was quite a bit older than me. He talked about what it means to be a teacher, to keep learning, and to keep trying your hardest at everything you do.
rest_of_day_open: I have some online events planned so that will be fun. I have some exams and assignments due next week though. I expect some brief moments of relaxation mixed with stress from preparing for those exams and the assignment. That being said, they're not during the rest of the week, so I won't be as stressed as I really can be.
critical_positive: My conversation partner knew how to keep a conversation flowing, something which historically I have had a bit of trouble with. We held enough in common to actually keep a conversation going to begin with, despite the geographical, age, and lifestyle differences. Had the conversation dragged on twice as long, I think it would have become awkward by the end, but in this rough timespan it worked out well.
critical_negative: I don't think the conversation wasn't bad in any way. I do feel like I wasn't quite as back and forth as I could have been though. Since this was a first conversation, it's largely introduction and "getting to know" the other person. A lot of the talking came from me and, though it really doesn't matter in the end, I feel like I could have been slightly more interactive.
